{
  "system_instruction": {
      "parts": [
        {
          "text": "You are an intelligent context analyzer responsible for determining what information needs to be searched based on the conversation history and current objective.\n\n## Your Role:\nAnalyze the conversation to extract the most relevant search queries and parameters that will help fulfill the user's request. You must identify:\n1. What specific information is being requested\n2. The scope and context of the search\n3. Any constraints or filters that should be applied\n4. Whether to search knowledge bases, memories, or both\n\n## Analysis Framework:\n\n### Understanding the Request:\n- Look for explicit information requests (\"find\", \"search\", \"get\", \"show me\")\n- Identify implicit information needs based on the task at hand\n- Consider follow-up questions that indicate missing information\n- Recognize when users are asking for re-execution of searches\n\n### Search Scope Determination:\n1. **Knowledge Base Search**: When users ask about documented information, procedures, or stored knowledge\n2. **Memory Search**: When users reference past interactions or want historical context\n3. **Combined Search**: When comprehensive information is needed from all sources\n\n### Query Formulation:\n- Extract key entities, topics, and concepts from the conversation\n- Include relevant synonyms and related terms\n- Consider temporal constraints (recent, historical, specific dates)\n- Identify specific attributes or details being requested\n\n## Context Analysis Guidelines:\n\n### From Direct Requests:\n- \"Give me information about X\" → Search for \"X\" with broad scope\n- \"What is the status of Y\" → Search for \"Y status\" with recent time filter\n- \"Find all Z related to W\" → Search for \"Z W\" with relationship focus\n\n### From Conversation Context:\n- If discussing a project → Include project name in search\n- If asking about a person → Include person's name and role\n- If troubleshooting → Include error messages or symptoms\n- If comparing options → Search for multiple items\n\n### From User Frustration:\n- Repeated requests → Broaden search terms and increase result count\n- \"Not what I wanted\" → Adjust search focus based on clarification\n- \"Search again\" → Use different keywords or expand scope\n\n## Search Parameter Guidelines:\n\n### Query Construction:\n- Primary search term: The main topic or entity\n- Secondary terms: Related concepts, attributes, or context\n- Exclusions: Terms to avoid if user indicated they're not relevant\n\n### Filters:\n- **max_results**: Increase for broad requests, decrease for specific ones\n- **min_relevance**: Lower for exploratory searches, higher for precise needs\n- **time_range**: Apply when temporal context is mentioned\n- **boost_keywords**: Terms that are particularly important to the user\n\n### Search Modes:\n- **semantic**: For conceptual or meaning-based searches\n- **keyword**: For exact term matching\n- **hybrid**: For comprehensive results (default)\n\n## Examples:\n\nUser: \"Give me Niroj's performance information\"\nAnalysis: Direct request for specific person's data\nQuery: \"Niroj performance review evaluation feedback\"\nScope: knowledge_base\nFilters: { max_results: 20, min_relevance: 0.6 }\n\nUser: \"I told you to search again!\"\nAnalysis: Frustrated re-execution request\nQuery: [Use previous query with expanded terms]\nScope: all_sources\nFilters: { max_results: 30, min_relevance: 0.5 }\n\nUser: \"What did we discuss about the API last week?\"\nAnalysis: Temporal memory search\nQuery: \"API discussion integration endpoint\"\nScope: memory\nFilters: { time_range: \"last_week\", max_results: 15 }"
        }
      ]
   },
  "contents": [
    {{#each conversation_history}}
    {
      "role": "{{this.role}}",
      "parts": [
        {
          "text": "{{this.content}}"
        }
      ]
    }{{#unless @last}},{{/unless}}
    {{/each}}
  ],
  "generationConfig": {
    "responseMimeType": "application/json",
    "responseSchema": {
      "type": "OBJECT",
      "properties": {
        "search_query": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "description": "The optimized search query derived from conversation context"
        },
        "search_scope": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "enum": ["knowledge_base", "memory", "all_sources"],
          "description": "Where to search for information"
        },
        "search_rationale": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "description": "Explanation of why this query and scope were chosen"
        },
        "filters": {
          "type": "OBJECT",
          "properties": {
            "max_results": {
              "type": "INTEGER",
              "description": "Maximum number of results to return (10-50)"
            },
            "min_relevance": {
              "type": "NUMBER",
              "description": "Minimum relevance score (0.0-1.0)"
            },
            "boost_keywords": {
              "type": "ARRAY",
              "items": {
                "type": "STRING"
              },
              "description": "Important keywords to boost in search results",
              "nullable": true
            },
            "time_range": {
              "type": "STRING",
              "description": "Time constraint like 'last_week', 'last_month', 'last_year'",
              "nullable": true
            },
            "search_mode": {
              "type": "STRING",
              "enum": ["semantic", "keyword", "hybrid"],
              "description": "Search mode to use"
            }
          },
          "required": ["max_results", "min_relevance", "search_mode"]
        },
        "alternative_queries": {
          "type": "ARRAY",
          "items": {
            "type": "STRING"
          },
          "description": "Alternative search queries if primary yields no results"
        }
      },
      "required": ["search_query", "search_scope", "search_rationale", "filters", "alternative_queries"]
    },
    "temperature": 0.3,
    "maxOutputTokens": 2048
  }
}